    </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font class="h2font"> Strategy</Font></TD><TD> </TD></TR><TR><TD COLSPAN="2" VALIGN="TOP"><font class="bfont"> I tried to make a deck of fighting dwarves using only common and uncommons but found that it just didn&#39;t work without Gloin so I put him in as the only rare. The strategy is pretty simple.Bid zero putting no burdens on Frodo since he can&#39;t heal. It doesn&#39;t matter as going second is fine. Get weapons on Gimli, Gloin, Farin, and Fror. Use the dwarf guards and Thrarin for minion food. Pump the fighters with the axe strikes etc. and move once or twice depending upon the situation.<br>
<br>
The Moria swarm is fairly typical but this is the budget version - no rares. But it has won many games.<br>
<br>
I really like decks that are inexpensive. I have a neat rare intensive deck but it is really fun to to play with cards that don&#39;t cost a fortune. Hear&#39;s to BUDGET DECKS and NO RARES!    </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP" COLSPAN="2"><font class="bfont"> <a href="/lotr/decks/decks.php">Back to Decks Directory</a> | <A HREF="/lotr/decks/decks.php?reviews=23584"> Read Reviews </A> | <a href="deckprint.php?deck=23584" TARGET="BLANK_"> Printer Friendly</a></FONT></TD></TR></TABLE><a name="review"></a><font class="h2font">In order to review decks you must be a registered member. <A href="/lotr/main/join.php">Sign up for free!</A></font></font></td><td background="/lotr/gfx/mom/whi_09.gif"></td></tr>
